# Justfile Standards for DaemonEye

## Task Runner Principles

Use DRY principles in justfile recipes as specified in [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md).

## Core Commands

- `just fmt`: Format all code with `cargo fmt --all`
- `just fmt-check`: Check formatting without modifying files
- `just lint-rust`: Run rustfmt check and clippy with zero warnings policy
- `just lint-just`: Lint the justfile itself
- `just lint`: Run all linting (rust + justfile)
- `just build`: Build the entire workspace
- `just check`: Check the workspace without building
- `just test`: Run all tests in the workspace

## Component-Specific Commands

- `just run-procmond args=''`: Run the procmond binary
- `just run-daemoneye-cli args=''`: Run the daemoneye-cli binary
- `just run-daemoneye-agent args=''`: Run the daemoneye-agent binary

## Shell Configuration

- Use `set shell := ["bash", "-eu", "-o", "pipefail", "-c"]` for strict error handling
- Ensure all commands fail fast on errors
- Use proper argument passing with `{{ args }}`

## Development Workflow

- Always run `just lint` before committing
- Use `just test` to validate changes
- Use `just build` to check compilation
- Use component-specific run commands for testing individual binaries
